<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

01:07.582 --> 01:09.749
♪

01:13.321 --> 01:15.589
America faces
an ominous new threat--

01:15.623 --> 01:17.457
<i>terrorism.</i>

01:17.492 --> 01:18.925
We must be vigilant,

01:18.960 --> 01:22.029
<i>secure every home,</i>
<i>every church,</i>

01:22.063 --> 01:24.931
<i>every Kwik-E-Mart</i>
<i>and presidential library.</i>

01:24.966 --> 01:26.266
PRESIDENT CLINTON:
<i>I grew up</i>

01:26.300 --> 01:27.567
in a little town in Arkansas,

01:27.602 --> 01:28.568
whose name, ironically,

01:28.603 --> 01:29.936
<i>was Terrorism.</i>

01:34.275 --> 01:35.809
(loud explosion)

01:37.612 --> 01:39.613
(explosion, television static)

01:41.616 --> 01:45.652
Ooh, there's new marshmallows
in the Belfast Charms!

01:45.686 --> 01:48.388
No! No, that's
Bart's cereal.

01:48.423 --> 01:51.958
It's the only way
I can get him to take

01:51.993 --> 01:54.261
his "vitamins."

01:54.295 --> 01:56.263
(sighs)

01:56.297 --> 01:58.265
Eat up.

01:58.299 --> 02:00.667
The sum of the square roots
of any two sides

02:00.701 --> 02:02.469
of an isosceles triangle
is equal

02:02.503 --> 02:04.104
to the square root
of the remaining side.

02:04.138 --> 02:05.906
That's not right.
Yes, it is.

02:05.940 --> 02:08.442
They're my lines as the
Scarecrow in <i>The Wizard of Oz.</i>

02:08.476 --> 02:11.078
Okay, I'm ready for
the Nuclear Workers Convention.

02:11.112 --> 02:14.681
It's a little sad-- the guys who
did the funny skit last year,

02:14.715 --> 02:16.316
well, they're all very sick.

02:16.350 --> 02:17.884
Did you pack
everything you need?

02:17.919 --> 02:19.152
Even better.

02:19.187 --> 02:22.389
I never unpacked from the time
we went to Hawaii.

02:26.360 --> 02:27.494
Whoo!

02:27.528 --> 02:29.996
My lava's almost cooled!

02:30.031 --> 02:32.099
(sizzling)

02:32.133 --> 02:33.166
(thump)

02:33.201 --> 02:35.602
I'm <i>still</i> cold.

02:35.636 --> 02:39.806
Oh, a whole weekend
away from my family.

02:39.841 --> 02:42.375
I can't believe
I have to miss taking the kids

02:42.410 --> 02:44.678
to buy gym uniforms.

02:44.712 --> 02:46.713
Send me a picture?

02:49.050 --> 02:50.183
Poor guy.

02:50.218 --> 02:51.852
Salt of the earth.

02:56.257 --> 02:59.159
ALL (chanting):
Convention! Convention!

02:59.193 --> 03:01.995
<i>Convention! Convention!</i>

03:02.029 --> 03:03.563
<i>Convention!</i>

03:03.598 --> 03:05.600
STEWARDESS:
<i>Oxygen masks on.</i>

03:05.625 --> 03:06.904
<i>Convention!</i>

03:07.394 --> 03:08.904
<i>Convention!</i>

03:16.591 --> 03:19.539
(air horn blasting,
siren blasting)

03:20.279 --> 03:21.684
Man I love conventions.

03:21.709 --> 03:24.580
Yeah, they’re the perfect combination
of work and binge drinking.

03:24.605 --> 03:27.220
Now look guys, we are here
for one important reason.

03:27.245 --> 03:29.100
To get free swag.

03:29.125 --> 03:32.775
Swag, I'm gonna
grab forever.

03:32.800 --> 03:35.759
Somethin' I really don't need.
Swag!

03:35.784 --> 03:38.652
I'm gonna have
40 key chains.

03:38.677 --> 03:41.081
And I don't even
have 40 keys.

03:41.106 --> 03:41.829
Swag!

03:41.854 --> 03:43.223
Interested in learning
a procedure

03:43.248 --> 03:44.673
that could save your life?

03:44.674 --> 03:47.240
♪ More free stuff  ♪

03:47.241 --> 03:49.176
♪ More free stuff  ♪
Uh, all I have are these spec sheets.

03:49.210 --> 03:50.410
♪ More free stuff,
more free stuff ♪

03:50.444 --> 03:52.579
ALL:
♪ Swag!

03:53.781 --> 03:55.482
(grunt, thud)

03:58.920 --> 04:01.121
(gasps) There's that
woman I always have

04:01.155 --> 04:03.590
a "same time next
year" affair with.

04:05.626 --> 04:07.060
And she's with
her frumpy friend

04:07.094 --> 04:08.962
I always have dinner with
when you two disappear.

04:08.996 --> 04:10.297
Mm-hmm-hmm.

04:10.331 --> 04:11.298
(slurps)

04:11.332 --> 04:14.067
Put up your nukes!
(chuckles)

04:14.101 --> 04:15.368
Halpern!

04:15.403 --> 04:17.370
Hey-hey! The wild
man of Wichita!

04:17.404 --> 04:18.772
I still haven't
forgiven you

04:18.805 --> 04:20.874
for putting that dead goat
in my bed.

04:20.908 --> 04:23.176
He wasn't dead till you
rolled over on him! Ha!

04:23.211 --> 04:24.311
(laughing): Oh, yeah.
Take that.

04:24.345 --> 04:25.812
In your face, boy.

04:25.846 --> 04:27.314
Ow! Ow!
Hey!

04:27.348 --> 04:28.982
(angry grunting)

04:29.016 --> 04:31.084
I'll kill you!
You son of a...!

04:31.118 --> 04:33.086
(deep panting)
Oh, come here, you.

04:33.120 --> 04:36.590
Oh...
Ah, yeah.

04:36.624 --> 04:41.995
It could be,
<i>if</i> we introduce

04:42.029 --> 04:44.331
Halpern, what will you
think of next?

04:44.365 --> 04:45.999
Nothing.
This is it.

04:46.033 --> 04:48.301
(slurring): Hey,
here's a brainstorm for you.

04:48.336 --> 04:52.005
Check if it's plugged in
before you call I.T.!

04:52.039 --> 04:54.341
You think I like
talking you monkeys

04:54.375 --> 04:56.509
through a password change?!

04:56.544 --> 04:57.510
(grunts)

04:57.545 --> 04:59.512
(laughter)

05:03.985 --> 05:05.986
(slurring):
To texting!

05:10.524 --> 05:11.925
Hello.

05:11.959 --> 05:13.760
Where's Homer?

05:13.794 --> 05:16.630
Homer, Homer-- when
<i>did</i> I see him last?

05:16.664 --> 05:17.631
Geez, I
don't know.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.032
(vomits)

05:19.066 --> 05:21.534
Yeah, Homer's a great guy,
but that doesn't mean

05:21.569 --> 05:24.204
I constantly think about
whether he's still alive or not.

05:29.443 --> 05:31.945
You're taking a picture of
'em in their moment of grief?

05:31.979 --> 05:33.179
It's okay.

05:33.214 --> 05:35.548
This camera has
an "auto cheer" feature.

05:37.351 --> 05:38.518
Aw...
Aw...

05:38.552 --> 05:40.520
Well, he's not
in the Boise morgue.

05:40.554 --> 05:42.722
Maybe he was mistaken
for a dead elephant

05:42.757 --> 05:44.858
and flown back to Kenya.

05:44.892 --> 05:46.860
You're talking
about my husband.

05:46.894 --> 05:49.896
To spare your feelings,
we'll just call him the Blob.

05:49.930 --> 05:52.271
Two to one says the Blob is

05:52.296 --> 05:54.566
stuck in the water-intake
pipe at the reservoir.

05:54.568 --> 05:58.705
Please, I need people here
who are helpful and sensitive.

05:58.739 --> 06:01.074
Sorry I'm late, everyone.
I had some trouble

06:01.108 --> 06:03.543
getting the voice mails
off the 9-1-1 line.

06:03.577 --> 06:06.046
Why does everyone have to talk
so fast and panicky?

06:06.080 --> 06:09.349
MAN (slowly and clearly):
A man with a gun is in my house.

06:09.383 --> 06:10.517
Gibberish.

06:10.551 --> 06:11.951
(barking)

06:16.223 --> 06:18.258
Hello, everyone.

06:18.292 --> 06:20.560
Homie! What happened to you?

06:20.594 --> 06:23.330
I overslept, lost my cell
phone, missed my flight.

06:23.364 --> 06:25.265
Why didn't you call us?

06:25.299 --> 06:27.267
Well, all the pay phones
at the airport

06:27.301 --> 06:29.235
were replaced
by self-serve yogurt.

06:29.270 --> 06:32.572
I ate all the cookie dough
toppings a man could want.

06:32.606 --> 06:35.575
So many cookies
will never be born.

06:35.609 --> 06:37.644
Well, I guess
all that matters is,

06:37.678 --> 06:40.680
everything's
back to normal.

06:40.715 --> 06:42.716
♪

06:49.657 --> 06:52.225
(explosion)

06:57.231 --> 06:59.933
Yes. Back to normal.

07:07.707 --> 07:09.341
Dear Christian God...

07:09.375 --> 07:11.843
Hey!
Sorry. Dear God--

07:11.878 --> 07:13.512
you know which
one I mean--

07:13.546 --> 07:15.914
thank you for
returning our Homie.

07:15.948 --> 07:19.151
He's still got a lot of
unfinished business down here.

07:20.620 --> 07:22.220
Amen.

07:22.255 --> 07:24.623
I'm glad you're back, Dad.

07:24.657 --> 07:27.559
It's hard to sleep
with one unkissed cheek.

07:27.593 --> 07:29.561
Yeah, it's tough being man
of the house.

07:29.595 --> 07:31.463
You left some big underpants
to fill.

07:31.497 --> 07:33.965
I didn't know they made
Underoos in size 52.

07:34.000 --> 07:35.901
They're called
Superoos, son.

07:35.935 --> 07:38.403
With pictures of the cast
of <i>The Expendables.</i>

07:38.438 --> 07:41.440
More like <i>The Expandables.</i>
(chuckles)

07:42.975 --> 07:44.543
Why didn't you
strangle me?

07:44.577 --> 07:47.779
That kind of small-scale
violence solves nothing.

07:47.814 --> 07:49.281
Couldn't agree more.

07:49.315 --> 07:50.882
Now to celebrate.

07:50.917 --> 07:54.920
Ta-da! Pork chops
crusted with Cheeto dust.

07:58.825 --> 08:01.526
Uh, I'll pass
on the pork.

08:01.561 --> 08:03.061
(spits)

08:05.598 --> 08:09.334
I'll just enjoy these green
beans with slivered almonds.

08:09.368 --> 08:11.970
Mmm, so slivered.

08:12.004 --> 08:14.005
Mmm.

08:16.976 --> 08:20.946
(quietly): Bart, why is the dad I always
wished for creeping me out?

08:20.980 --> 08:24.549
I don't know. 'Cause you're
incapable of experiencing joy?

08:24.584 --> 08:26.118
Yay.
(groans)

08:26.152 --> 08:27.519
Point taken.

08:27.553 --> 08:29.788
Dad, what's that
on your lap?

08:29.822 --> 08:30.956
A napkin.

08:30.990 --> 08:32.457
(others gasp)

08:34.494 --> 08:36.094
Glad you're back, buddy.

08:36.129 --> 08:38.462
You got a lot
of catching up to do.

08:45.204 --> 08:47.172
(grunting, panting)

08:47.206 --> 08:49.775
Can I just get a glass of water?

08:49.809 --> 08:52.277
Water? That stuff killed
my grandmother.

08:52.311 --> 08:54.980
So sad.

09:00.319 --> 09:01.887
I've been having

09:01.921 --> 09:04.156
snuggle dreams.

09:04.190 --> 09:07.159
Marge, I changed in Boise.

09:07.193 --> 09:10.162
I'm not sure a man
who eats right and doesn't drink

09:10.196 --> 09:11.563
can be good in bed.

09:11.597 --> 09:13.999
Well, what made you...?
You're so beautiful

09:14.033 --> 09:17.169
when I cut you off in
the middle of a question.

09:17.203 --> 09:19.437
(both moaning)

09:20.473 --> 09:22.941
(gasps)
Oh. Oh, my.

09:22.975 --> 09:24.743
What's that thing
you're doing?

09:24.777 --> 09:27.179
HOMER (sultrily):
Moving my body.

09:27.213 --> 09:29.681
MARGE (chuckling):
Oh.

09:29.715 --> 09:33.251
(humming happily)

09:33.286 --> 09:35.887
Don't you think it's weird
that Dad stopped eating pork

09:35.922 --> 09:37.322
<i>and</i> drinking beer?

09:37.356 --> 09:38.824
Who cares
what happened?

09:38.858 --> 09:40.358
Daddy's back.

09:40.393 --> 09:42.127
(grunts)

09:43.362 --> 09:44.963
(humming happily)

09:54.106 --> 09:56.575
Something happened to Dad
on that trip.

09:56.609 --> 09:58.410
This is worse than when he went
to New Orleans

09:58.411 --> 10:00.712
and came back
with a Southern accent.

10:00.746 --> 10:03.215
(deep Southern accent):
Uh, how y'all doin'?

10:03.249 --> 10:05.417
(crunch)

10:06.419 --> 10:08.887
(dog barking in distance)

10:08.921 --> 10:11.321
Chief Wiggum, how come every
time there's a terrorist chatter

10:11.324 --> 10:13.725
in this town, you come to me?
Lay off, Apu.

10:13.759 --> 10:15.727
When I look at people,
I don't see colors.

10:15.761 --> 10:18.630
I just see crackpot religions.
Chief, is there

10:18.664 --> 10:21.066
really a terrorist threat
to Springfield?

10:21.100 --> 10:24.469
Yeah. I got
a very important phone call.

10:24.503 --> 10:26.271
(phone rings)
Yello?

10:26.305 --> 10:28.106
MAN:
Is this line secure?

10:28.140 --> 10:30.775
Uh, it's a little jiggly
but it'll hold.

10:30.810 --> 10:34.613
We got intel-- uh, that's short
for a word I don't know...

10:34.647 --> 10:36.781
Intelligence?
I don't believe so, no.

10:36.816 --> 10:40.886
Anyway, this intel says that
someone in town has been turned

10:40.920 --> 10:43.488
and they're working for terrorists.
(gasps)

10:43.522 --> 10:46.391
Now, I got to go check
my other suspects.

10:46.425 --> 10:48.226
Uh-huh.

10:48.261 --> 10:50.362
But I may be back.

10:53.599 --> 10:56.101
Huh?

10:56.135 --> 10:59.104
(gasps)
Dad's kneeling on a prayer mat.

10:59.138 --> 11:01.773
He doesn't believe in kneeling.

11:01.807 --> 11:05.443
(chanting indistinctly)

11:05.478 --> 11:08.513
Huh? It looks like he's praying.

11:09.548 --> 11:12.117
To the east. The Middle East.

11:12.151 --> 11:13.785
Mecca.

11:20.793 --> 11:22.894
(quietly): He's targeting
the nuclear plant.

11:27.700 --> 11:29.668
Meow?

11:29.702 --> 11:31.937
If you are a cat, prove it.

11:31.971 --> 11:34.940
Do you hate Mondays,
like Garfield? (screeches)

11:34.974 --> 11:37.842
And do you love lasagna,
like me?

11:37.877 --> 11:39.277
Meow.

11:39.312 --> 11:41.346
Okay then.

11:41.380 --> 11:42.714
(humming happily)

11:46.319 --> 11:48.887
Mom, I have to tell you
something about Dad,

11:48.921 --> 11:50.121
something big!

11:50.156 --> 11:53.491
I know. He's changed.

11:53.526 --> 11:54.559
Exactly.

11:54.593 --> 11:55.794
For the better.

11:55.828 --> 11:57.362
And men don't
change that way.

11:57.396 --> 11:58.069
But-but...

11:58.094 --> 11:59.831
Do you know what
we're doing on Sunday?

11:59.832 --> 12:02.367
Brunch with the Hibberts.
Then the tile store.

12:02.401 --> 12:06.771
He's like a husband
in a widow's memory-- perfect.

12:06.806 --> 12:09.407
(grunting)

12:09.442 --> 12:11.409
Perfect.

12:11.444 --> 12:13.678
Perfect.

12:18.384 --> 12:21.586
(beeping)

12:21.620 --> 12:23.922
(phone rings)
FBI.

12:23.956 --> 12:26.157
I think someone I love
is a terrorist.

12:26.192 --> 12:27.759
Does that make me crazy?

12:27.793 --> 12:29.761
No, no. Not at all.

12:29.795 --> 12:32.764
It took me two hours to get
home. Traffic was <i>crazy.</i>

12:32.798 --> 12:34.599
Are you people
talking about me?

12:34.633 --> 12:36.768
No. We're not even
here right now.

12:47.813 --> 12:49.781
742 Evergreen Terrace.
I'll be right there.

12:49.815 --> 12:51.716
And don't believe what
you've heard about me.

12:51.751 --> 12:54.753
I haven't heard anything
about you except from you.

12:56.455 --> 12:59.624
Hanging up
the receiver, eh?

12:59.658 --> 13:01.526
(gasps)
How much did you hear?

13:01.560 --> 13:02.861
How much did you say?

13:02.895 --> 13:03.928
Nothing, really.

13:03.963 --> 13:06.097
So I heard half of nothing.

13:06.132 --> 13:09.134
Dad, you're scary
when you're calm and focused.

13:09.168 --> 13:11.870
Lisa, I'll miss you
when this is all over.

13:11.904 --> 13:13.238
When what's all over?

13:13.272 --> 13:15.240
This conversation.
(chuckles nervously)

13:15.274 --> 13:17.442
See you on the other side.

13:17.476 --> 13:18.777
What other side?

13:18.811 --> 13:20.712
Of the house.
Where the fireplace is.

13:20.746 --> 13:22.447
We're toasting marshmallows.

13:22.481 --> 13:24.215
Marsh...

13:24.250 --> 13:26.451
mallows.

13:37.045 --> 13:39.013
I'm Bart Simpson.
Who the hell are you?

13:39.047 --> 13:40.848
Agent Crawford, FBI.

13:40.882 --> 13:43.083
You guys know I don't talk
to field agents.

13:43.118 --> 13:44.919
Get your boss on the phone.

13:44.953 --> 13:47.554
I'm not here for you.
I'm here for your dad.

13:47.589 --> 13:49.556
What do you want
with his dad?

13:49.591 --> 13:51.191
Go back to
sleep, Milhouse.

13:51.226 --> 13:52.593
How do you know my name?

13:52.627 --> 13:55.129
I didn't. But I do now.

13:56.131 --> 13:58.299
Don't talk.
Okay.

13:58.333 --> 13:59.967
I want you to know
I'm the best there is

14:00.001 --> 14:01.392
at finding out
what you're up to.

14:01.417 --> 14:02.002
Ooh.

14:02.003 --> 14:04.138
I can torture you.
I can give you incredible sex.

14:04.172 --> 14:06.373
Or you can just tell me
what I want to know.

14:06.408 --> 14:07.384
What was the
first one again?

14:07.409 --> 14:08.409
I see.

14:08.410 --> 14:10.210
You're stupid.
Hey.

14:10.245 --> 14:12.212
I'm the one in bed
with two beautiful women.

14:12.247 --> 14:13.213
(gasps)

14:13.248 --> 14:16.150
You think
I'm beautiful? Oh!

14:16.184 --> 14:18.118
In a breaking-and-entering
kind of way.

14:18.153 --> 14:20.120
Well, give me something,
or I'm not leaving.

14:20.155 --> 14:21.889
(snoring)

14:21.923 --> 14:25.326
Let's just say I've got
to get to work on time.

14:25.360 --> 14:28.729
And if you knew me, you'd know
just how odd that sounds.

14:28.763 --> 14:30.597
Who are you
talking to?

14:30.632 --> 14:32.166
No one.

14:32.200 --> 14:35.302
You're in too deep, Annie.
Get out.

14:35.337 --> 14:37.304
Are you real, or my imagination?

14:37.339 --> 14:39.707
Either way,
my advice is sound.

14:41.309 --> 14:43.944
I love my job.

14:43.979 --> 14:48.349
HOMER (à la Islamic call
to prayer): ♪ It is the climax

14:48.383 --> 14:50.284
♪ What everything's been

14:50.318 --> 14:54.755
♪ Buil...

14:54.789 --> 14:56.323
♪ Di-ing to

14:56.358 --> 15:01.362
♪ Hope it pays off for you

15:01.396 --> 15:02.796
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh.

15:02.831 --> 15:04.298
(beeping)

15:04.332 --> 15:05.666
What you got there, Homer?

15:05.700 --> 15:07.201
Weird thing
under a tarp.

15:07.235 --> 15:09.870
That's what I thought.
Have a good one. (laughs)

15:09.904 --> 15:12.539
You laugh now, but
you won't be laughing soon.

15:12.574 --> 15:14.508
He's right,
because now I go back

15:14.542 --> 15:16.977
to remembering
that my cat just died.

15:17.012 --> 15:19.513
He's in.
(knocking)

15:19.547 --> 15:22.349
One sunrise
burrito, please.

15:22.384 --> 15:23.317
Fine!

15:26.154 --> 15:28.389
FEMALE VOICE:
Facial recognition required.

15:28.423 --> 15:29.823
(high-pitched whirring)

15:29.858 --> 15:31.592
Welcome, Mr. Burns.

15:44.439 --> 15:45.806
(grunts)
Dad?

15:45.840 --> 15:47.474
Huh? How'd you get in here?

15:47.509 --> 15:49.877
Girl Scout cookies
get you in anywhere.

15:49.911 --> 15:51.311
Please don't do this, Dad.

15:51.346 --> 15:53.514
I don't know what horrors
you saw in Boise,

15:53.548 --> 15:55.916
but it's not worth
blowing up everyone you love.

15:55.950 --> 15:57.418
I'm not blowing up the plant.

15:57.452 --> 15:58.819
(chuckling):
Oh.

15:58.853 --> 16:00.254
Just harmlessly stopping it

16:00.288 --> 16:02.723
from doing more damage
to Mother Earth.

16:02.757 --> 16:04.158
Is that something

16:04.192 --> 16:06.093
your terrorist masters
told you to tell me?

16:06.127 --> 16:07.761
(sighs)
Yes.

16:07.796 --> 16:10.998
My terrorist masters are always
talking about you, Lisa.

16:11.032 --> 16:15.302
<i>I missed my flight,</i>
<i>so I got in a van...</i>

16:21.242 --> 16:23.210
<i>...with some eco-friendly</i>
<i>activists.</i>

16:23.244 --> 16:25.345
<i>They wanted gas, grass or ass,</i>

16:25.380 --> 16:27.881
<i>and, brother, I had the ass.</i>

16:27.916 --> 16:30.250
They taught me something
I found shocking.

16:30.285 --> 16:33.387
Pigs aren't happy
to be made into pork chops.

16:33.421 --> 16:35.722
This T-shirt lied to me.

16:35.757 --> 16:39.393
And they also gave me
an alcohol detox.

16:39.427 --> 16:41.495
♪ Nothing's shakin'
on Shakedown Street ♪

16:43.698 --> 16:45.899
♪ Used to be the heart of town

16:47.902 --> 16:50.871
♪ Don't tell me this town
ain't got no heart... ♪

16:50.905 --> 16:52.606
Oh! Oh!

16:52.640 --> 16:56.376
Oh, I've been listening
to this song for three days,

16:56.411 --> 16:59.613
and it's only the end
of the first verse!

16:59.647 --> 17:01.882
LISA:
<i>But I saw you praying to Mecca.</i>

17:01.916 --> 17:04.785
Lisa, I've never prayed
to a city in my life,

17:04.819 --> 17:07.721
and if I did, it would be
Hershey, Pennsylvania.

17:07.755 --> 17:10.824
I was kneeling on the
affirmation rug they gave me.

17:11.659 --> 17:13.594
See?

17:13.627 --> 17:15.162
(rhythmically): Ow, this rug is hard
on my knees.

17:15.195 --> 17:16.597
Ow, this rug is
hard on my knees.

17:16.631 --> 17:17.964
Ow, this rug is hard
on my knees.

17:17.999 --> 17:20.434
But wait, wait, wait.
What is this?

17:20.468 --> 17:22.736
Lisa, the most horrible truth
of all is,

17:22.770 --> 17:26.440
the plant where I work poisons
our water and our air.

17:26.473 --> 17:28.742
I've told you that
a million times.

17:28.776 --> 17:32.446
Aw, sweetie, you told me a
thousand things a million times.

17:32.480 --> 17:35.182
Even with a brain
the size of a dinosaur's,

17:35.216 --> 17:36.950
I couldn't take that in.

17:36.985 --> 17:38.752
Anyhoo, this canister

17:38.786 --> 17:41.822
is full of spoiled milk
and utility-grade chicken,

17:41.856 --> 17:44.458
both sold to me by Apu
this morning.

17:44.492 --> 17:45.826
When I release it

17:45.860 --> 17:47.594
into the AC system,

17:47.629 --> 17:49.930
it'll stink up
the plant forever.

17:49.964 --> 17:53.100
No one can use it,
but no one gets hurt.

17:53.134 --> 17:55.836
Just like
when I smell up the toilet.

17:55.870 --> 17:56.837
(knocking)
(gasps) Huh?

17:56.871 --> 17:58.839
(grunting)

17:58.873 --> 17:59.840
(door opens)

17:59.874 --> 18:00.841
There he is.

18:00.875 --> 18:02.709
Use your fattest handcuffs.

18:02.744 --> 18:04.511
Hey. Uh, it's not
what you think, Lou.

18:04.546 --> 18:05.646
Lou, Lou, Lou.

18:05.680 --> 18:06.647
(ululating):
Lou-Lou-Lou-Lou-Lou...!

18:06.681 --> 18:08.015
(groans)

18:08.049 --> 18:10.117
I can complete my dad's mission

18:10.151 --> 18:12.719
just like George W. Bush.

18:12.754 --> 18:15.522
I can't shoot a little girl.

18:15.557 --> 18:17.124
(gunshot)
Ah, damn it!

18:17.158 --> 18:18.692
There's some things
they just don't teach you

18:18.726 --> 18:22.262
in the police academy... movies.

18:23.331 --> 18:25.632
(distorted grunting)

18:29.737 --> 18:30.704
(electronic trilling)

18:30.738 --> 18:32.172
(rhythmic chugging)

18:33.708 --> 18:35.509
We did it, Dad. We did it.

18:35.543 --> 18:36.877
We sure did.

18:36.911 --> 18:37.878
(grunts)

18:37.912 --> 18:40.180
You weren't shot.

18:40.215 --> 18:42.916
No, I was just up late
watching a movie.

18:42.951 --> 18:45.719
Something with
William Holden and...

18:45.753 --> 18:47.054
(snoring)

18:51.926 --> 18:53.894
Your plan failed.

18:53.928 --> 18:55.249
Thank God this
plant has never had

18:55.263 --> 18:56.663
a functioning
air conditioner.

18:56.698 --> 18:58.365
Wait a minute, Burns.

18:58.399 --> 19:00.167
You don't have a functioning
AC system at a nuclear plant?

19:00.201 --> 19:01.568
That's against the law.

19:01.603 --> 19:03.203
That's impossible.

19:03.238 --> 19:05.005
Smithers, didn't we move
this plant to China?

19:05.039 --> 19:06.406
Sir, that's two years from now,

19:06.441 --> 19:07.908
and you're not supposed
to tell anyone.

19:07.942 --> 19:08.976
Oopsie.

19:10.712 --> 19:13.113
There isn't a prison made
that can hold me.

19:13.147 --> 19:15.282
Prisons are still made
of mud and wattles, right?

19:15.316 --> 19:18.919
No. Concrete.
(gasps loudly)

19:18.953 --> 19:21.255
You know, Dad, just because
your mission's complete,

19:21.289 --> 19:24.291
it doesn't mean you have
to go back to pork eating

19:24.325 --> 19:26.727
and beer... drinking.

19:26.761 --> 19:28.862
A beer from the sky!

19:28.896 --> 19:31.265
It's a sign!

19:31.299 --> 19:32.699
(laughing)

19:34.068 --> 19:36.036
Yeah, this equipment will pay
for itself

19:36.070 --> 19:37.671
in one night of binging.

19:40.808 --> 19:44.611
I wish a mission could bring me
closer to someone, but it can't.

19:44.646 --> 19:47.748
Okay, it's time for me
to walk alone into the sunset.

19:48.983 --> 19:50.384
(gulps loudly)

19:50.418 --> 19:51.985
That's better.

19:57.158 --> 19:59.593
(groans)

20:13.232 --> 20:16.234
Amazingly, the hamster's
older than I am.

